rbr: yes][day: yes]; 3 or 4 salmon trollers in the area; lots of "herring-like" (50-70 m deep)and scattered echosign 20 m off bottom; blue fuzz layer at 10 m; net went through vertically stretched herring-like school at approx. 9 to 20 m depth and the blue fuzz layer and a second herring-like school, so hauled back at 15 minutes.

rbr: yes][day: yes]; had to tow at southern end of block because the top end of the block is too shallow for a surface tow. A lot of blue fuzz echosign between 40 m and the bottom; quite thick in places and with herring-like schools at aboutu 70-80 m depth.

rbr: yes][day: yes]; blue fuzz echosign throughout the water column and concentrated at near bottom (60 m) and smallish herring-like echosign centered at 20 m (one of which looked like it went into the net just prior to doors being locked; at 18:55).  A couple more looked like they went in the net after the doors were locked; hauled back because it looked like a lot of fish went into the net and the FM is having difficulty keeping the net at the surface due to the current. Not sure that this is a surface tow, because the net was up and down quite a bit.

rbr: yes][day: no]; blue fuzz echosign throughout the water column and herring like schools from 15 to 30 m that we ran through.  We ran through multiple schools, looks like a lot going into the net, so hauled back early.

rbr: yes][day: no]; light blue fuzz echosign throughout water column, but thicker below 40 m depth. Not too much went into the net (as seen by the sounder) until about 1 minute left in the tow and we caught part of a huge herring-like school (massive echosign between 9 and 20 m)
rbr: yes][day: no]; had to tow on one side of block because a tug was coming through
rbr: yes][day: yes]; a lot of blue fuzz echosign in the top 20 m and herring-like school echosign near the bottom
rbr: yes][day: yes]; blue fuzz echosign centered on ~9 m depth
rbr: yes][day: yes]; blue fuzz echosign down to 15 or 20 m; similar to last tow (where we caught ~100 adult salmon), so hauled back a bit early
rbr: yes][day: no]; FOGGY; too many fish here, hauled back early; visual estimate 2000 kg
rbr: yes][day: no]; FOGGY; too many fish in area, so hauled back early
rbr: yes][day: no]; full moon!  too many fish in area, so hauled back early.

rbr: yes][day: yes]; bridle was twisted on deployment (just after doors went into the water), so had to haul back at 16:11 and started re-setting at 16:23.  lots of blue fuzz echosign down to 25 m depth.  Quite a bit of echosign going into net, particularly in last 10 minutes of the tow.
rbr: yes][day: yes]; light blue fuzz echosign to about 25 m depth

rbr: yes][day: yes]; schools at the surface; caught part of one on deployment (prior to locking doors); current making it difficult to keep the net at 15 m (port door is at the surface and the starboard door is at 20 m); lots going into the net, so hauled back early. I messed up the time of gear retrieval, but we towed for 10 minutes and I got the end retrieval time, so think the recorded times are now correct. Ooops - not much catch  - so surprising.
rbr: yes][day: no]; a lot a lot a lot of stuff going into the net; not sure if it's fish, based on the last tow, but got nervous and hauled back early.

rbr: yes][day: no]; lots of echosign going into net, but the EK80 38 kHz shows blue fuzz without much colour in it. So going to tow for 20 and see what happens. There was a lot going in the net and under the net - dark red/concentrated returns, butjudging from the last tow, we are thinking it may be euphausiids (?!)  YES, it was euphausiids and shrimp!! Mixed with salmon and herring.
rbr: yes][day: yes]; blue fuzz echosign in top 30 m; with current and swell, difficult to keep net at surface; one door at surface and one at 20 m.
rbr: yes][day: no]; FULL MOON! Light blue fuzz echosign at the surfact to 40 m depth.
